mil.nga.giat.geowave.index.dimension

Class LongitudeDefinition

  • java.lang.Object
    • mil.nga.giat.geowave.index.dimension.BasicDimensionDefinition
      • mil.nga.giat.geowave.index.dimension.LongitudeDefinition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NumericDimensionDefinition, Persistable

    public class LongitudeDefinition
extends BasicDimensionDefinition
    The Longitude Definition class is a convenience class used to define a dimension which is associated with the X axis on a Cartesian plane. Minimum bounds = -180 and maximum bounds = 180

        public BinRange[] getNormalizedRanges(NumericData range)
        Method is used to normalize the ranges on a Cartesian plane. If the values are outside of the bounds [ -180, 180 ], two Bin ranges might be created to account for the possible date line crossing.
